It may be possible that your computer connects to your routers DNS address.
When you plug into your cable modem you of course get a different DNS server.
Your router may not be updating but it should in time.
Your computer may also play a roll in that.
In the mean time you can manually edit your host file on your computer Your host file is located: C:\WINDOWS\system32\drivers\etc open the file HOSTS in notepad and make your changes.
Example configuration 74.125.95.104 www.google.com #Comment google.com 74.125.95.104 google.com #your own comment
